title: 609. 10 Takeaways from Week 9
itunes:title: 609. 10 Takeaways from Week 9
description:
Daniel Jeremiah, Bucky Brooks and Rhett Lewis look back at the weekend and pick ten storylines that stood out from Week 9 of the NFL season. To start off, the guys look at how Bills QB Josh Allen went off in a win over the Seahawks (1:35). Next, the trio discuss why everyone should pump the brakes on the Buccaneers' Super Bowl bid after their loss to the Saints (5:04). Later, the guys break down Dolphins QB Tua Tagovailoa and Cardinals QB Kyler Murray's matchup (18:59). To wrap up the show, DJ, Bucky and Rhett talk about how the Falcons showed some life in a victory over the Broncos and why the team could consider interim head coach Raheem Morris for their head coaching vacancy (36:29). All that and more in this packed episode.
